collaboration arts at stanford university presented by sica home search this site arts enews subscribe for students collaboration student groups stanford is home to roughly 90 arts related student organizations 65 of which are performance based the groups span all genres including visual arts film music drama dance publications and magazines public and community service plus event organizing presenting and support much of the programming on campus is a result of the rich and diverse body of student organizations in the arts most students find themselves regularly attending arts events in which their friends are performing or helping organize in the spring the student organizing committee for the arts soca an umbrella student arts organization presents an annual three day long festival in white plaza in conjunction with students for a sustainable stanford called vision earth which many performance groups and individual artists and musicians on campus participate in throughout the year you will find quarterly shows or weekly concert series as well as many other ways to engage creatively with campus culture and community the student arts & entertainment calendar is the best place to find out about student programming starting a new group so you can t find a group that accomplishes your goals want to start your own student group the office of student activities osa has a comprehensive checklist on how to accomplish just that be sure to get some of your interested friends and colleagues to help you start a group is not a group without people click here for their guide and remember you don t need to wait for the administration to ok your group to start planning though for many funding resources and for reserving some spaces you will need to be a registered vso gook luck new to stanford if you are considering becoming more involved in the arts at stanford you may want to explore the arts guide a multi media guide to all arts organizations departments and student groups on campus videos slideshows and text information are presented for each group the arts guide provides a great sense of the diversity culture and opportunities campus has to offer in the arts each year organizations have a chance to update their videos and information in the guide every april the guide is mailed to all prospective freshmen if the arts guide influenced your choice in deciding to come to stanford send an email to studentarts stanford edu and tell us about it view the arts guide online party on the edge at cantor arts center prospective students check out the arts guide your multimedia guide to the arts at stanford stay updated student home events calendar opportunities in review subscribe curricular info majoring minoring creativity course guide arts intensive arts immersion arts circle make it happen money supplies space collaboration promotion beyond stanford internships career resources bay area arts back to arts at stanford make a gift volunteer login press sitemap contact connect twitter facebook vimeo flickr 2011 stanford university all rights reserved local user login
